      serialVersionUID:
      1L

      • Serialized Fields

        • theLayout

          FlowLayout theLayout
          Layout for the panel.

        • nextButton

          JButton nextButton
          Button to move to next card.

        • showLeftButton

          JButton showLeftButton
          Button to show left hidden side of the card.

        • showCenterButton

          JButton showCenterButton
          Button to show the center (visible) of the card.

        • showRightButton

          JButton showRightButton
          Button to show right hidden side of the card.

        • leftCorrectButton

          JButton leftCorrectButton
          Button to mark left hidden side of the card as correct.

        • rightCorrectButton

          JButton rightCorrectButton
          Button to mark right hidden side of the card as correct.

        • leftState

          CorrectIncorrectEnum leftState
          State of the left button (mark correct or mark incorrect).

        • rightState

          CorrectIncorrectEnum rightState
          State of the right button (mark correct or mark incorrect).

        • leftTitle

          String leftTitle
          String (minus "Correct" or "Incorrect") in left correct button.

        • rightTitle

          String rightTitle
          String (minus "Correct" or "Incorrect") in right correct button.

        • leftInitCorrect

          boolean leftInitCorrect
          Set to true if the left side of the card was initially marked correct when first displayed. This will be set to false the first time the side is marked incorrect and will not be set to true on subsequent marking of the side correct. This will provide an indication as to whether or not to display a dialog asking the user to confirm setting the side incorrect.

        • rightInitCorrect

          boolean rightInitCorrect
          Set to true if the right side of the card was initially marked correct when first displayed. This will be set to false the first time the side is marked incorrect and will not be set to true on subsequent marking of the side correct. This will provide an indication as to whether or not to display a dialog asking the user to confirm setting the side incorrect.
